                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Guatemala/80: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-23T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 23, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Your despatch No. 640, May 8, 1935.<note n="43" xml:id="d298fn43">Not
                        printed.</note> We are disappointed at the delay in receiving a definite
                    reply from the Guatemalan authorities. Please inform them that French Government
                    has now closed St. Pierre-Miquelon to the smuggling traffic, effective May 15,
                    and that we hope for an early and favorable reply stating that the Government of
                    Guatemala will take prompt steps, in line with those already taken by Canada,
                    Cuba, Great Britain and France, to prevent the further use of its territory as a
                    smuggling base.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
